# Mind The Kid - Project Rules

## Project Structure
- `src/` - Source code and application logic
- `data/` - Data files, datasets, and data-related resources such as SQL files
- `iac/` - Infrastructure as Code (Terraform, CloudFormation, etc.). This project uses Terraform.
- `scripts/` - Utility scripts and automation tools

## General Guidelines
- Follow consistent naming conventions across all directories
- Document all major changes and decisions
- Use meaningful commit messages
- Keep dependencies up to date
- Test thoroughly before committing changes

## Code Quality
- Write clean, readable, and maintainable code
- Include appropriate comments and documentation
- Follow language-specific best practices
- Use linting and formatting tools
- Implement proper error handling

## Security
- Never commit sensitive information (API keys, passwords, etc.)
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Follow security best practices for your technology stack
- Regularly review and update dependencies

## Collaboration
- Review code before merging
- Communicate changes clearly
- Help maintain project documentation
- Respect coding standards and conventions 